<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910627-0090</DOCNO><DOCID>910627-0090.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Sunrise Technologies Outlook</HL><DATE>06/27/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C6</SO><CO>   SNRS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>MEDICAL AND BIOTECHNOLOGY, GENETIC RESEARCH, PROSTHETICS (MTC)</IN><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   FREMONT, Calif. -- Sunrise Technologies Inc. expects toreport record revenue for the second quarter and per-shareearnings more than four times higher than in the year-earlierperiod.   The company cited continued strong sales of its dental andophthalmology laser systems for an expected increase inrevenue to $4.6 million from $1.4 million a year ago. It saidnet income should exceed the nine cents a share reported inthe first quarter. The company wouldn't be specific about netincome, but nine cents a share would be more than four timeslast year's second-quarter earnings of two cents a share.</LP><TEXT>   The company also said negotiations are under way to expandits manufacturing facilities to meet the continuing highlevel of orders. It is expected that the new production spacewill be occupied during the fourth quarter.</TEXT></DOC>